The paper deals with connectivity and network design problems in graphs, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Game Theory (cs.GT). The abstract mentions Steiner forests, which are a classic problem in computational geometry, and spider-decomposition, which is a technique used in game theory. The paper also discusses graph reduction techniques, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
